
JSLint plugin for jEdit
=======================

INSTALL

Choose "Plugin Manager..." in jEdit's Plugins menu.  On the "Install" tab,
Choose JSLintPlugin


MANUAL INSTALL

1. Copy JSLint.jar into your jEdit "jars" folder, which is normally at
   %USERPROFILE%\.jedit\jars or $HOME/.jedit/jars

2. Open jEdit, and choose "Plugin Manager..." on the Plugins menu.
   Check the box next to JSLint.jar.


CONFIGURATION

In jEdit, choose "Plugin Options..." from the Plugins menu.  Select JSLint in
the tree view and modify options as required.


THANKS

Thank you to Douglas Crockford (www.crockford.com) for JSLint.

Thank you to Jiger Patel for the jEdit plugin 'CodeLint' which was used as a
basis when this plugin was developed.


